===Etymology===
Here are some proposals:
*{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} reconstructs {{och-l|脈|tr= {{IPAfont|*mrêk}}}} (← *''mer-k'' or rather *''mər-k''), proposes its cognacy to {{cog|lus|mar||pulse, pulse's beating}} and a {{der|zh|sit}} origin for both.
*{{zh-ref|Baxter & Sagart (2014)}} relate {{och-l|脈|tr= {{IPAfont|*C.m'<r>[i]k}}|vein}} to {{och-l|淢|tr= {{IPAfont|*m̥(r)ik}}|rapid stream}} ~ {{och-l|洫|tr= {{IPAfont|*m̥(r)ik}}|ditch, moat}}. 
**They additionally relate {{och-l|脈|tr= {{IPAfont|*C.m'<r>[i]k}}|vein}} to {{och-l|血|blood|tr= {{IPAfont|*m̥ˤik}}}}, yet {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2019)}} criticizes Baxter & Sagart for "phonetic over-interpretation of graphs" to reconstruct Old Chinese pronunciation ''*m̥ˤik'' for {{zh-l|血*}} and for confusing etymological link with mental association between "blood" and "vein".

